                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      SAIL-Posco JV date
          OUR BUREAU                              
	New Delhi, July 16: Steel Authority of India Ltd (SAIL) is likely to ink a pact with South Koreas Posco by October to jointly set up plants at an investment of Rs 15,000 crore.        
	Both SAIL and Posco teams are working on it. A joint venture deal could be signed in the next three months, SAIL chairman C. S. Verma told reporters on the sidelines of the 23rd meeting of the National Steel Consumers Council here.        
	Steel secretary Atul Chaturvedi, who was present at the meeting, said, A framework agreement for the joint venture between the two companies will be signed next month.        
	SAIL and Posco have inked an MoU for developing steel plants in the country. An integrated 1.5-million-tonne-per-annum steel plant is proposed to be developed at Bokaro, Jharkhand, at an estimated investment of Rs 11,000 crore.                                                                                                                                                          
